[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring method handles**\n\nI’m thinking about Native Image and whether method handles need reflection registration. It’s not entirely clear to me because if a method is only reachable through a method handle string, might the native analysis overlook it? I want to confirm that the findVirtual method is properly doing a run-time dynamic lookup. There seems to be some complexity in how it's all connected, so I want to make sure I’m getting it right!\n\n**Considering MethodHandles usage**\n\nThe user pointed out there's no direct reflection in tests, which makes me think about how MethodHandles relate to that. I wonder if I can use lambdas or serialization, but it seems like I can't. When they say \"Do not use reflection directly,\" it probably means I shouldn't use things like Class.forName or getDeclaredMethod, but I might still have some options with MethodHandles. I like that I don't need native guards, which is good! I'll ensure to use top-level public and use AssertJ for my assertions.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09fb1eb58e0e3b740169f00d504bb88192988e896273360937\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8A1iU_0yxJsC6wfdyniyzsaR988uNSxv3_0Pln37jUoTGs7P1lUExeho0Pz24gEZ8cdh7pf7G73MciMcdr_7iETVkmDG6V_E9hUAI81Q_uQEZluy_2zIqu56HIHUdV_nBFRs9jlMrp6pU94Rdnl2jqkzl1Rec-zEOndGvuQ93ofq014j4QVJK51YPyKArmD_mkvgp80jIOUikx0SBRbUerjKyXJAs_bainhvxnAi8y_YCMMq_NmQ40TebvA9Z5GpVin8UJaqyVL2tcxLYpaC_06OVdQ3-McPMctmEUBET8WcnmKMJU3-ZXQVFeiw2GXIJZ97LKk6ueQ7ZVuqiL1uLoGBii_CCv2gPjblC-5fjWVRk2nUwjobRQ-mkRhmxENIOvuUIjz7Z_q-_LvygaIxvYjkITpted0q1WeOmK-zCy-9QysKCEPU4bapqd8DGnSKrThrp1qvey13vaF-MkSRv5nvdsq6IB00WPO37yv4xUF_JJQx73aboBCYgWdDApqGXdJ3TnUJZk7H7kJ2LG0hnHLgThS7b2Flb092NTf1Xp9puyknydZlfmeoEevH76Cl1s206k2tHVkWDD60ulHdX8lRgT8E7BPp7q5vHSCx4E_dPyneHMcQRQvcPFBuZHAypPc-VAEmD2e7gOUrBWmyxSR63woE1v1HsEU9UfOTat9seq6GvIcwBneBPNsiSf2btFWc67AyJYX24CbQuj2Ipa5zgNiJTTeWwHQ